        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
159.808g/mol is the molar mass of bromine (Br2). 
959.1714g/mol is the molar mass of decabromodiphenyl ether (C12Br10O). 

The production of decabromodiphenyl ether is a batch reaction of bromine and diphenyl ether with the aid of a catalyst. The reaction requires temperatures of approximately 59 degrees Celsius (Pakalin 2007). The catalyst is not consider significant in terms of emissions for the reaction and it is therefore not included in this dataset and it is assumed to be taken into consideration in the input of chemical factory.
Chemical reaction:
10Br + C12H10O -&gt; C12Br10O + 5H2, the assumed conversion efficiency is 0.90.</comment>
